title: HL-60_exo-1
characteristics_ch1.1: cell type: malignant myeloid cell line
growth_protocol_ch1: Human CD34+ cord-blood progenitors (New York Blood Center) were enriched using MACS cell separation (Miltenyi Biotec) and cultured in serum-free media (Stem Cell Technologies) supplemented with 100U/ml penicillin/streptomycin, 40ng/ml FLT3L, 25ng/ml SCF, and 50ng/ml TPO (Miltenyi Biotec) at 1% oxygen and 5% carbon dioxide for 48h, after which exosomes were isolated by differential centrifugation. HL-60 and MOLM-14 cell lines were cultured at 1% oxygen and 5% carbon dioxide in RPMI + 10% FBS and 1X Pen-Strep for 48 hours, after which extracellular vesicles were isolated by differential centrifugation.
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted using the Qiagen miRNeasy kit according to the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated RNA was prepared using Affymetrix HSR miRNA Flash Tag Biotin protocol with 130 ng total RNA input
hyb_protocol: Hybridizations were performed as per Affymetrix FlashTag Biotin HSR RNA Labeling Kit User Guide with incubation at 48掳C/ 60 rpm for 18 hours. Arrays were washed and stained on Fluidics Station 450 using script FS450_0002
scan_protocol: Standard Affymetrix scan protocol using GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G
data_processing: Data were analyzed with Partek Genomics Suite(v.6.6) using the RMA normalization method. Four samples from GEO accession GSE55025 (GSM1328048, GSM1328049, GSM1328044, GSM1328045) were included along with twelve new samples for the normalization.
